book:


 Hack Async MySQL
 Async Mysql


  &reftitle.intro;


   Hack’s async functions allow an application to continue executing code while fetching data, which can dramatically reduce the time it spends waiting for IO. MySQL is usable with Hack’s async functions.



   This support comes from a new MySQL client library from the WebScaleSQL project; this is built-in to HHVM and will work with any recent MySQL server.



   There are 11 classes associated with async MySQL:


AsyncMysqlClient

AsynMysqlConnectionPool

AsyncMysqlConnection

AsyncMysqlResult

AsyncMysqlErrorResult

AsyncMysqlQueryErrorResult

AsyncMysqlQueryResult

AsyncMysqlRowBlock

AsyncMysqlRowBlockIterator

AsyncMysqlRow

AsyncMysqlRowIterator




    This extension is bundled directly with HHVM.



